  "prompt": "Where can I update the latest FIFA squad 14 for PC offline?",
  "response": "To update the latest FIFA 14 squad for PC offline, you can use the following methods:\n\n1. **Download Online Squads**: \n   - You can find forums and websites where other players share updated squad files. Websites like **FIFA Infinity** or **Soccer Gaming** often have patches or squad updates that you can download.\n   - Look specifically for squad updates that are compatible with FIFA 14.\n\n2. **Using Creation Master 14**:\n   - Creation Master 14 is a tool that allows you to edit FIFA 14, including rosters and squads. You can download this program, then manually update player stats, transfers, etc. You can find updated databases on community forums.\n\n3. **Manual Updates**:\n   - Using the in-game editor, you can manually update players and squads based on the latest information from reliable sources like transfer news websites.\n\n4. **Community Patches**:\n   - The FIFA community often creates patches to update teams and players. Search for FIFA 14 mods or patches, and download one that includes the latest squads.\n\n5. **Backup Your Original Files**:\n   - Always backup your original squad files before applying any updates, as this allows you to restore the game if something goes wrong.\n\nOnce you download an update or patch, follow the provided instructions to install it. Usually, this involves placing the downloaded files in a specific folder in the FIFA 14 directory. Always ensure any mod or patch you download is from a reputable source to avoid malware.",
